programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1967: Packers vs. Chiefs
programme.desc: From 1967: Green Bay vs. Kansas City in Super Bowl I in Los Angeles. Green Bay beat the AFL champions 35-10 behind three second-half TDs. Bart Starr earned MVP honors, passing for 250 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1968: Packers vs. Raiders
programme.desc: From 1968: Green Bay vs. Oakland in Super Bowl II in Miami. Green Bay won 33-14 for its second-straight title. This was Vince Lombardi's last game as coach of the Packers. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1969: Colts vs. Jets
programme.desc: From 1969: New York Jets vs. Baltimore in Super Bowl III in Miami. The Jets beat the overwhelmingly favored Colts 16-7 behind QB Joe Namath, who had guaranteed a victory. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1970: Chiefs vs. Vikings
programme.desc: From 1970: Kansas City vs. Minnesota in Super Bowl IV in New Orleans. The Chiefs dominated the game to beat Minnesota 23-7. QB Len Dawson earned MVP honors. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1971: Colts vs. Cowboys
programme.desc: From 1971: Baltimore vs. Dallas in Super Bowl V in Miami. The Colts won 16-13 on Jim O'Brien's field goal with five seconds remaining. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1972: Cowboys vs. Dolphins
programme.desc: From 1972: Dallas vs. Miami in Super Bowl VI in New Orleans. The Cowboys won 24-3 behind Roger Staubach, who threw for 119 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1973: Dolphins vs. Redskins
programme.desc: From 1973: Miami vs. Washington in Super Bowl VII in Los Angeles. The Dolphins won 14-7. Jake Scott had two interceptions, including one in the end zone, to be named MVP. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1974: Dolphins vs. Vikings
programme.desc: From 1974: Miami vs. Minnesota in Super Bowl VIII in Houston. The Dolphins won their second-straight Super Bowl 24-7. Larry Csonka rushed for 145 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1975: Steelers vs. Vikings
programme.desc: From 1975: Pittsburgh vs. Minnesota in Super Bowl IX in New Orleans. Franco Harris ran for 158 yards and a TD in the Steelers' 16-6 victory. Pittsburgh's defense held the Vikings to 119 total yards. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1976: Steelers vs. Cowboys
programme.desc: From 1976: Dallas vs. Pittsburgh in Super Bowl X in Miami. The Steelers won 21-17 for their second-straight title. Terry Bradshaw connected with Lynn Swann on a 64-yard TD pass. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1977: Raiders vs. Vikings
programme.desc: From 1977: Minnesota vs. Oakland in Super Bowl XI in Pasadena, Cal. The Raiders won 32-14 to claim their first Super Bowl. Pete Banaszak ran for two touchdowns. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1978: Cowboys vs. Broncos
programme.desc: From 1978: Dallas vs. Denver in Super Bowl XII in New Orleans. Defense lifted Dallas to a 27-10 victory as the Cowboys recovered four fumbles and intercepted four passes. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1979: Steelers vs. Cowboys
programme.desc: From 1979: Pittsburgh vs. Dallas in Super Bowl XIII in Miami. Terry Bradshaw threw 4 TD passes to lift the Steelers over Dallas 35-31. John Stallworth caught 2 TD passes. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1980: Steelers vs. Rams
programme.desc: From 1980: Pittsburgh vs. Los Angeles Rams in Super Bowl XIV in Pasadena, Cal. Pittsburgh beat the Rams 31-19 to become the first team to win four Super Bowls. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1981: Raiders vs. Eagles
programme.desc: From 1981: Oakland vs. Philadelphia in Super Bowl XV in New Orleans. The Raiders rode Jim Plunkett's arm to a 27-10 victory. Plunkett threw for 261 yards and 3 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1982: 49ers vs. Bengals
programme.desc: From 1982: San Francisco vs. Cincinnati in Super Bowl XVI in Pontiac, Mich. The 49ers won 26-21. Ray Wersching booted four field goals. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1983: Redskins vs. Dolphins
programme.desc: From 1983: Washington vs. Miami in Super Bowl XVII in Pasadena, Cal. The Redskins came from behind to win 27-17 after trailing 17-10 at halftime. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1984: Raiders vs. Redskins
programme.desc: From 1984: Los Angeles Raiders vs. Washington in Super Bowl XVIII in Tampa. The Raiders won 38-9 as Marcus Allen rushed for 191 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1985: 49ers vs. Dolphins
programme.desc: From 1985: San Francisco vs. Miami in Super Bowl XIX in Stanford, Cal. The 49ers won 38-16 to capture their second-straight title. Joe Montana captured his second MVP award. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1986: Bears vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 1986: Chicago vs. New England in Super Bowl XX in New Orleans. The Bears rode an overpowering defense to a 46-10 victory. Chicago racked up 7 sacks and held the Pats to 7 rushing yards. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1987: Giants vs. Broncos
programme.desc: From 1987: New York Giants vs. Denver in Super Bowl XXI in Pasadena, Cal. The Giants topped the Broncos 39-20. Phil Simms was 22-for-25 for 268 yards and 3 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1988: Redskins vs. Broncos
programme.desc: From 1988: Washington vs. Denver in Super Bowl XXII in San Diego. The Redskins won 42-10 after scoring on five-straight possessions in the second quarter. QB Doug Williams threw for 340 yards and 4 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1989: 49ers vs. Bengals
programme.desc: From 1989: San Francisco vs. Cincinnati in Super Bowl XXIII in Miami. The 49ers won 20-16 to capture their third Super Bowl. Jerry Rice caught 11 passes for 215 yards on his way to winning MVP honors. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1990: 49ers vs. Broncos
programme.desc: From 1990: San Francisco vs. Denver in Super Bowl XXIV in New Orleans. The 49ers cruised 55-10 to capture their second-straight title. QB Joe Montana earned MVP honors for the third time after going 22-for-29 for 297 yards and 5 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1991: Giants vs. Bills
programme.desc: From 1991: New York Giants vs. Buffalo in Super Bowl XXV in Tampa. The Giants won 20-19. Buffalo's Scott Norwood missed a 47-yard field goal with seconds remaining. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1992: Redskins vs. Bills
programme.desc: From 1992: Buffalo vs. Washington in Super Bowl XXVI in Minneapolis. The Redskins rode Mark Rypien's arm to a 37-24 win. Rypien threw for 292 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1993: Cowboys vs. Bills
programme.desc: From 1993: Dallas vs. Buffalo in Super Bowl XXVII in Pasadena, Cal. The Cowboys turned nine turnovers into 35 points in a 52-17 rout over Buffalo. Troy Aikman threw 4 TD passes and Buffalo lost its third-straight Super Bowl. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1994: Cowboys vs. Bills
programme.desc: From 1994: Dallas vs. Buffalo in Super Bowl XXVIII in Atlanta. This rematch of Super Bowl XXVII was won by Dallas 30-13, as the Bills lost their fourth-straight Super Bowl. Emmitt Smith ran for 132 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1995: 49ers vs. Chargers
programme.desc: From 1995: San Francisco vs. San Diego in Super Bowl XXIX in Miami. Steve Young threw for 6 TDs and 325 yards as the 49ers prevailed 49-26 to win their fifth Super Bowl title. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1996: Steelers vs. Cowboys
programme.desc: From 1996: Pittsburgh vs. Dallas in Super Bowl XXX in Tempe, Ariz. The Cowboys struck early and often to win 27-13, scoring on their first three possessions. Larry Brown intercepted two Pittsburgh passes in the second half. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1997: Packers vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 1997: New England vs. Green Bay in Super Bowl XXXI in New Orleans. The Packers topped New England 35-21. Desmond Howard scored on a 99-yard kickoff return and earned MVP honors. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1998: Broncos vs. Packers
programme.desc: From 1998: Denver vs. Green Bay in Super Bowl XXXII in San Diego. John Elway earned his long-awaited first championship by leading the Broncos to a 31-24 win. Terrell Davis ran for 3 TDs and 157 yards. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 1999: Broncos vs. Falcons
programme.desc: From 1999: Denver vs. Atlanta in Super Bowl XXXIII in Miami. Denver won 34-19 as John Elway threw for 336 yards and a touchdown and ran for another score in his final game before retiring. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2000: Rams vs. Titans
programme.desc: From 2000: Tennessee vs. St. Louis in Super Bowl XXXIV in Atlanta. The Rams won their first title with a 23-16 win over Tennessee. MVP QB Kurt Warner threw for 414 yards and 2 TDs. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2001: Ravens vs. Giants
programme.desc: From 2001: Baltimore vs. New York Giants in Super Bowl XXXV in Tampa. The Ravens' defense paved the way for a 34-7 victory. Baltimore allowed just 152 yards, forced five turnovers and had four sacks. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2002: Rams vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2002: New England vs. St. Louis in Super Bowl XXXVI in New Orleans. The Patriots won 20-17 on Adam Vinatieri's 48-yard field goal as time expired. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2003: Buccaneers vs. Raiders
programme.desc: From 2003: Tampa Bay vs. Oakland in Super Bowl XXXVII in San Diego. The Bucs romped to a 48-21 victory after returning 3 INTs for TDs and recording five sacks. Dwight Smith was named MVP with 2 TDs on INT returns. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2004: Patriots vs. Panthers
programme.desc: From 2004: New England vs. Carolina in Super Bowl XXXVIII in Houston. The Pats won 32-29 on an Adam Vinatieri field goal with four seconds remaining. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2005: Eagles vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2005: New England vs. Philadelphia in Super Bowl XXXIX in Jacksonville. New England won 24-21 to claim its third championship in four years. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2006: Steelers vs. Seahawks
programme.desc: From 2006: Pittsburgh vs. Seattle in Super Bowl XL in Detroit. Hines Ward caught five passes for 123 yards and scored a 43-yard TD off a reverse that sealed the Steelers' 21-10 victory. It was the fifth Super Bowl victory for Pittsburgh. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2007: Colts vs. Bears
programme.desc: From 2007: Indianapolis vs. Chicago in Super Bowl XLI in Miami. RBs Dominic Rhodes and Joseph Addai combined to rush for 190 yards and Kelvin Hayden returned an INT for a TD in the Colts' 29-17 victory. Thomas Jones ran for 112 yards for the Bears. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2008: Giants vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2008: New York Giants vs. New England in Super Bowl XLII. The Giants ended 18-0 New England's quest for a perfect season with a 17-14 upset. The win was sparked by a stellar defensive effort and a long TD drive in the final minutes directed by Eli Manning. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2009: Cardinals vs. Steelers
programme.desc: From 2009: Arizona vs. Pittsburgh in Super Bowl XLIII. The Steelers won 27-23 for their sixth Super Bowl victory. Santonio Holmes caught the winning TD with 35 seconds remaining. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2010: Colts vs. Saints
programme.desc: From 2010: Indianapolis vs. New Orleans in Super Bowl XLIV. The Saints overcame an early deficit to win a 31-17 decision. QB Drew Brees completed 32 of 39 passing attempts for the Saints. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2011: Packers vs. Steelers
programme.desc: From 2011: Green Bay vs. Pittsburgh in Super Bowl XLV. The Packers won 31-25, with Aaron Rodgers throwing 3 TD passes. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2012: Giants vs. Patriots
programme.desc: From 2012: New York Giants vs. New England in Super Bowl XLVI. The Giants won 21-17, with game MVP Eli Manning engineering a come-from-behind fourth-quarter touchdown drive. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2013: 49ers vs. Ravens
programme.desc: San Francisco vs. Baltimore in Super Bowl XLVII. The Ravens won 34-31 in New Orleans. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: 2014: Broncos vs. Seahawks
programme.desc: Denver vs. Seattle in Super Bowl XLVIII. (cc)(n)

programme.title: Super Bowl Highlights: Super Bowl XLIX: New England Patriots vs. Seattle Seahawks
programme.sub-title: Super Bowl XLIX: New England Patriots vs. Seattle Seahawks
programme.desc: New England vs. Seattle in Super Bowl XLIX. Tom Brady led the Patriots comeback, with the win capped by the game-ending interception by Malcolm Butler at the 1-yard line to seal the 28-24 victory. (cc)(n)
